text: Batik Air is an Indonesian scheduled airline which was founded in 2012. It made its first flight on 3 May 2013 from Jakarta to Manado and Yogyakarta. As of September 2019, Batik Air flies more than 45 domestic and international routes, with over 350 flights daily. International destinations, including Singapore, Bangkok, Chennai, and Perth, as well as Guilin, Nanning, Kunming and Shenzhen in China. ==References== Category:21st-century establishments in Indonesia Category:2012 establishments in Asia Category:Airlines of Indonesia
